          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p><strong>Problem Overview</strong></p>",
            "<p>In this Problem, students use similar triangles to measure distances on the ground that cannot be measured directly. The Student Edition provides a diagram to illustrate this idea. However, if possible, you can reenact the Problem in a  real‑life setting.</p>",
            "<p>Students revisit what it means for triangles to be similar. They recall that they can use similar triangles, and the scale factor between the triangles, to find unknown corresponding lengths. They apply these ideas in finding an inaccessible distance across a river.</p>"
          ]
        }
